author: Violet Law
title: As coronavirus spreads, few leads but many theories on origin
description: Coronavirus most likely to have jumped to humans from intermediary host, but some say lab accident cannot be ruled out.
content:
Hong Kong, China - The blame game between China and the United States on the origin of the COVID-19 pandemic has overshadowed the role public-health laboratories in China have played in the outbreak.
